import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['people'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of population over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    age_sex_population = data.pivot_table(index='age', columns='sex', values='people', aggfunc='sum')
    age_sex_population.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=plt.gca())
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of population across different age groups and sex?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
